  <p class="lead">
    Located just south of Crystal Lake. Personal, privately owned pet care — rooted right here in this community.
  </p>

  <p>
    I still remember my first visit to my husband's hometown. Driving through the winding, tree-lined streets by the Dole Mansion, walking along the lake, experiencing a small-town, close-knit feeling nestled in the Northwest suburbs — there was no better place to raise our four daughters, establish roots, and start a small private animal hospital from scratch. The largest city in McHenry County and just 45 miles from Chicago, Crystal Lake became our home and the foundation for Healthy Paws Animal Hospital. We sit adjacent to the southwest corner of Crystal Lake, a 5 minutes drive from Huntley Rd. and Ackman Rd., close enough to feel like your neighborhood vet, because in every way we are.
  </p>

  <p>
    Our mantra since opening in 2010 has been "Come experience veterinary medicine in a whole new way." As a team we live and breathe this philosophy. Large corporate chains and high-volume practices have become the norm. We decided to be the opposite, treating patients as unique individuals, and clients the way we would want to be treated ourselves. This is our neighborhood; our clients are our community. The patients we care for are the dog or cat just down the street, the ones we see on a walk or at a soccer game, the ones we hear about at the grocery store or a local restaurant. That connection is what we believe makes us different from any other animal hospital in the area.
  </p>

  <h2>Supporting Crystal Lake Pet Owners</h2>

  <h3>Fighting Fear</h3>
  <p>
    When choosing a veterinarian, while credentials and location matter, equally important is how your pet and you feel before, during, and after a visit. It does not matter how many titles a doctor has, or how fancy their equipment, if they cannot effectively explain options to you as an owner, take the time to answer your questions, or support you when you are most worried for your pet. If your pet is terrified and the veterinary team is not able to help them in a supportive way their health is put at risk. Nervous pets often lead to preoccupied owners limiting their ability to absorb the information being presented in the exam room. This is one of the reasons why we liken a trip to Healthy Paws to a trip to grandma's house, lots of treats and positive attention to help calm everyone's nerves!
  </p>
  <p>
    Spending time with families and using a variety of calming techniques for our patients sets us up for success. From care coordinators taking clients directly to an exam room, providing multiple forms of treats (liver treats, peanut butter, whipped cream, string cheese, and more!), veterinary technicians asking detailed questions, and our veterinarians explaining how to best help your pet — in this hospital, care is a team effort.
  </p>

  <h2>Options for Crystal Lake Pet Owners</h2>

  <h3>Education First and Always</h3>
  <p>
    I love learning, I love teaching, I love veterinary medicine. The combination of all three is just plain fun. We do not expect clients to understand everything that is happening with their pets, that is our job. Our goal is for owners to leave our practice with a better grasp of their pet's health than when they arrived, knowing they have choices, support, and resources. We explain our physical exam findings in real time, provide options and discuss pros and cons, and we let owners know what to watch for if things are not going as planned. We believe that our team and clients are empowered by learning and strive to incorporate it into everything we do.
  </p>

  <h2>Comfort for Crystal Lake Pet Owners</h2>

  <h3>A Hospital That Doesn't Have to Feel That Way</h3>
  <p>
    We do not have a large waiting area or lobby, but instead a front door, a welcoming smile, and an immediate escort to an exam room. It can be stressful enough coming to the doctor without having to face multiple strangers, smells, and sounds. There is no reason for cats and dogs to experience this when seeing the veterinarian. At Healthy Paws Animal Hospital we have treats galore as well as floor-to-ceiling windows in our exam rooms allowing owners and pets to see the light of day and providing much-needed calm. There is no paying your bill in public with your pet anxiously trying to get out the door, in-room checkout allows every part of your visit to happen in one private location and provides the opportunity for you to ask any additional questions or just absorb all the information presented.
  </p>

  <h2>Comprehensive Services for Crystal Lake Pet Owners</h2>

  <h3>Complete Care, Private Care</h3>
  <p>
    Crystal Lake pet owners have access to a full range of veterinary services at Healthy Paws Animal Hospital. This all while making sure your pet and you know you are our primary focus, the way medicine should be. Being privately owned, our hospital makes your pet's health care about the individual, not the bottom line.
  </p>
