  <h2>Community for Crystal Lake Pet Owners</h2>

  <h3>Dog Friendly Finds</h3>
  <p>Looking for some fun places to take your dog in Crystal Lake? Here are a few suggestions:</p>
  <p>
    <strong>Hound Town Dog Park</strong> — A 3-acre, fully fenced, off-leash dog park inside Lippold Park Sport Complex. Requires registration, vaccination records, and a keycard. Lippold is also a great spot for on-leash walks with your pup.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Veterans Acres Park</strong> — Wooded hiking trails where leashed dogs are welcome. Beautiful for a nature walk. Don't forget to check for ticks and use preventative — Veterans Acres is an amazing trek, but not without potential tick exposure.
  </p>

  <h3>Dog-Friendly Dining &amp; Drinks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Crystal Lake Brewing</strong> — Dogs are welcome on the patio. They keep dog mats and cookies on hand. Genuinely dog-friendly, not just tolerant. Bring something for the humans to share with each other also.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>The Cottage</strong> — Seasonal dog-friendly patio with pub fare, burgers, tacos, and more. A local favorite.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Cafe Olympic</strong> — Outdoor sidewalk seating and a dedicated dog menu. Yes, really.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Julie Ann's Frozen Custard</strong> — Seasonal spot where you and your dog can both get a treat. Every day brings a new flavor.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Starbucks (Northwest Highway)</strong> — Puppuccinos available on request. Outdoor, pet-friendly tables.
  </p>

  <h3>Cats About Town</h3>
  <p>
    While cats may not get to visit a dog park or patio restaurant, they have their own local resources. An important reminder for cat owners: make sure your pet's microchip information is current. If your feline decides to take a walkabout in Crystal Lake, an updated chip is the fastest way back home.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Thomas' Tails</strong> — A family-owned natural pet food store in the heart of historic downtown Crystal Lake. Quality food, treats, toys, and accessories for cats — and three resident cats in the store. A neighborhood treasure worth visiting. (31 E Crystal Lake Ave)
  </p>

  <h3>Thinking of Adding a Cat to Your Family?</h3>
  <p>Crystal Lake has wonderful adoption resources close to home.</p>
  <p>
    <strong>McHenry County Animal Control &amp; Adoption Center</strong> — The county's official adoption center, located right in Crystal Lake. Cats are spayed or neutered, vaccinated, and microchipped before adoption.
  </p>

